UNITED STATES of America, Plaintiff-Appellee, v. Rafael Alberto CADENA-SOSA, Defendant-Appellant. No. 15-10362

Non-Argument Calendar.

United States Court of Appeals, Eleventh Circuit. Nov. 19, 2015. Wifredo A. Ferrer, Adam C. McMichael, Kathleen Mary Salyer, U.S. Attorney’s Office Miami, FL, for Plaintiff-Appellee. Michael B. Cohen, Michael B. Cohen, PA, Fort Lauderdale, FL, for Defendant-Appellant. *895Before WILLIAM PRYOR, JORDAN and JILL PRYOR, Circuit Judges. PER CURIAM:

Michael B. Cohen, appointed counsel for Rafael Alberto Cadena-Sosa in this appeal, has moved to withdraw from further representation of the appellant and has filed a brief pursuant to Anders v. California, 386 U.S. 738, 87 S.Ct. 1396, 18 L.Ed.2d 493 (1967). Our independent review of the entire record reveals that counsel’s assessment of the relative merit of the appeal is correct. Because independent examination of the entire record reveals no arguable issues of merit, counsel’s motion to withdraw is GRANTED, and Cadenar-Sosa’s convictions and sentences are AFFIRMED.
